OL,3,CEngland fans allowing themselves to be
OL,4,C'optimistic' ahead of Ghana match
OL,6,FAhead of the match at the Gillette
OL,7,FStadium in nearby Foxborough, Adam
OL,8,FParkinson, 32, from Barnsley, told the
OL,9,FPress Association: "It's a once-in-a-
OL,10,Flifetime type of thing, it's England
OL,11,Fat a World Cup.
OL,13,F"We saved up ` we kind of had it in
OL,14,Fmind to come.
OL,16,F"My brother lives in Canada, so we
OL,17,Fthought 'the World Cup's there, we're
OL,18,Fgoing to go, let's think about it' and
OL,19,Fthen we priced it up and we thought
OL,20,F'OK, that's going to be a bit more
OL,21,Fmoney than we had in mind'.
OL,26,@qD@TOUuD@AOUxD@AOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/15
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,304,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30305
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F303A1782181080
OL,3,CEngland fans allowing themselves to be
OL,4,C'optimistic' ahead of Ghana match
OL,6,F"It's one of them, right? You've just
OL,7,Fgot to do it sometimes."
OL,9,FOn England's chances, Mr Parkinson
OL,10,Fsaid: "We played well in the first
OL,11,Fone, so we can be optimistic for once."
OL,13,FCameron Gray, 28, from Essex, said he
OL,14,F"can't wait" to experience Boston
OL,15,Fafter hearing about the city from his
OL,16,FScottish father, who attended
OL,17,FScotland's matches there earlier in
OL,18,Fthe tournament.
OL,20,FHe said: "I was born in England so
OL,21,FI've only ever known English.
OL,26,@nD@AOUoD@XO]rD@GOUsD@gO]vD@AOUvD@LO]|D@
OL,26,AJOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/15
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,304,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30306
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F303A1782181080
OL,3,CEngland fans allowing themselves to be
OL,4,C'optimistic' ahead of Ghana match
OL,6,F"I've got a warm heart for the Scots,
OL,7,Fbut England's mine."
OL,9,FHe added: "My dad was actually here in
OL,10,FBoston and he said it was amazing so I
OL,11,Fcan't wait."
OL,13,FAsked what his father thought of him
OL,14,Fsupporting England, Mr Gray said:
OL,15,F"He's never actually put it on me, so
OL,16,Fhe accepts it."
OL,18,FHe said England needed to play the
OL,19,Fsame as they did in the second half
OL,20,Fagainst Croatia to secure a win
OL,21,Fagainst Ghana.
OL,26,@nD@AOUoD@TO]qD@KOUsD@LO]wD@AOUxD@OO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/15
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,304,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30307
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F303A1782181080
OL,3,CEngland fans allowing themselves to be
OL,4,C'optimistic' ahead of Ghana match
OL,6,F"We need to attack, attack, attack,"
OL,7,Fhe said.
OL,9,F"I know that's a cliche, but our
OL,10,Fattack is, I'd say, the best in the
OL,11,FWorld Cup.
OL,13,F"We've got the best striker in the
OL,14,Fworld, it's as simple as that."
OL,16,FDespite the high costs for those
OL,17,Ftravelling from the UK, Three Lions'
OL,18,Ffans based in the US said the game was
OL,19,Ftheir first opportunity to see the
OL,20,Fteam at a World Cup.
OL,26,@nD@AOUnD@dO]qD@AOUuD@AOUvD@_O]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/15
